<br>
A wizard that tries to fight a melee by standing there and swapping melee blows does not even deserve the title. Do you think in pvp we are going to stand there and take hits as someone pounds on us?! Hell no, we are going to reply in kind and in whatever manner it takes to make you see a Loading..Please wait message before we get dropped.<br>
<br>
Here is a list of classes that have dropped to my wizzie, actually both my lighty wiz and my dark (take a pick I take turns playing one or another):<br>
<br>
Shadow Knights<br>
Necros w/ pet or without<br>
Bards<br>
Clerics<br>
Warriors bwahaha<br>
Rogues<br>
Druids <br>
Shamans w/pet or without<br>
Mage <br>
Enchanter w/pet or without<br>
<br>
and the list keeps going. Does that mean Im a god? No, but I certainly dont stand in one spot and wait to be hit. It would be like 2 boxers facing each other in the ring and not blocking each other from blows. It isnt going to happen in that ring, it certainly is NOT going to happen in game. Have I lost some good fights? Hell ya, but I tell them it was a good fight and move on.<br>
<br>
Kudos to the wizzies that dont take this cr*p standing still but make people earn their worth on pvp-that means less braggarts on how wizzies are so 'easy' to pk. <br>
<br>
Ive lvld both my wizzies to 50 and 55 respectively , Im not sure yet about lvl 60 for my wizard, but I certainly pounded a lvl 59 Mage at lvl 52 a while back. Scarey eh? Last words: &quot;holy sh8t&quot;, im glad he was a good sport about it all; to be honest I think it was luck on that kill but at the least I didnt get famous tells like &quot;you are ajlkfadsjlf Im going to kick your bu!$&quot;...its getting old.<br>
<br>
How is this, it doenst matter what class you play, its the person behind that keyboard that makes a class rock. Hell, I have seen clerics be monsters in pvp, if that isnt scarey, I dont know what is. Every time I was thinking about quitting on my wizzie through all my levels I would always see the impossible, like one wizard in SrO fighting 5 peeps and kicking their arse, and yes, he killed each and every one of them. (geezuz) It was enough to keep lvling and learning pvp. Have fun fellow nukers! (salutes)<br>
And dont take the hits standing still....hehe<br>
